1
00:00:02,500 --> 00:00:05,470
Your results are in, Ms. Monou.

2
00:00:05,470 --> 00:00:08,340
According to our diagnosis,

3
00:00:08,340 --> 00:00:10,720
you are infertile.

4
00:00:10,720 --> 00:00:12,720
I'm...

5
00:00:13,720 --> 00:00:15,630
infertile?

6
00:00:15,630 --> 00:00:17,690
I wanted to stay with you forever, Sui.

7
00:00:17,690 --> 00:00:19,920
But when my parents saw your records...

8
00:00:19,920 --> 00:00:21,970
They told me the marriage was off.
[Diagnosis]

9
00:00:21,970 --> 00:00:23,250
If she's infertile,

10
00:00:23,250 --> 00:00:26,540
doesn't that mean you two can do it raw?

11
00:00:26,540 --> 00:00:27,600
That's a big win!

12
00:00:27,600 --> 00:00:29,670
They're practically saying

13
00:00:29,670 --> 00:00:33,360
you've failed as a woman.

14
00:00:35,720 --> 00:00:37,730
Don't bother putting one on.

15
00:00:37,730 --> 00:00:40,830
I'll be fine.

16
00:00:40,830 --> 00:00:42,140
What are you talking about?

17
00:00:42,140 --> 00:00:45,330
These are for protecting your body.

18
00:00:55,060 --> 00:00:57,220
<i>Your door is now locked.</i>

19
00:01:01,240 --> 00:01:03,660
Guess that wasn't all for us, huh?

20
00:01:06,220 --> 00:01:07,890
Thank you.

21
00:01:07,890 --> 00:01:10,490
That's all for us.

22
00:01:18,970 --> 00:01:21,350
Why are you...

23
00:01:21,350 --> 00:01:23,570
I live here.

24
00:01:23,570 --> 00:01:25,680
- Does that mean...
- <i>Your door is now locked.</i>

25
00:01:25,680 --> 00:01:28,060
We're now neighbors, and coworkers.

26
00:01:28,060 --> 00:01:29,810
Welcome to the dorm.

27
00:01:32,580 --> 00:01:35,150
Don't be shocked.
You're the one who transferred in.

28
00:01:35,150 --> 00:01:36,690
What?

29
00:01:36,690 --> 00:01:40,750
I'm Erika's cousin, Mao Tsukidome.

30
00:01:40,750 --> 00:01:42,390
Nice to meet you.

31
00:01:44,470 --> 00:01:46,040
It's your first day, right?

32
00:01:46,040 --> 00:01:48,730
Follow me.
I'll show you a shortcut to the office.

33
00:01:50,750 --> 00:01:52,530
Th-Thank you.

34
00:02:17,340 --> 00:02:20,160
Is this really happening?

35
00:03:31,390 --> 00:03:32,360
[Idea Construction Office]

36
00:03:32,360 --> 00:03:37,230
This is Sui Monou, our newest team member.

37
00:03:37,230 --> 00:03:40,650
My name is Sui Monou.
It's nice to meet you all.

38
00:03:43,200 --> 00:03:47,430
I'll have Mizuno and Mao teach you the ropes.

39
00:03:53,920 --> 00:03:55,880
This is our cafe space.

40
00:03:55,880 --> 00:03:59,170
You're free to take any of the drinks here.

41
00:03:59,170 --> 00:04:00,510
Thank you.

42
00:04:00,510 --> 00:04:03,640
This shelf is for our reference books,

43
00:04:03,640 --> 00:04:06,450
and mail is to be placed here.

44
00:04:06,450 --> 00:04:07,940
I see.

45
00:04:07,940 --> 00:04:10,110
Mizuno. I'll take it from here.

46
00:04:10,110 --> 00:04:13,500
- Huh?
- I have plenty of work to explain.

47
00:04:13,500 --> 00:04:15,410
- Follow me.
- Right.

48
00:04:15,410 --> 00:04:17,860
Thank you again.

49
00:04:17,860 --> 00:04:19,550
Take a seat.

50
00:04:24,570 --> 00:04:26,630
For starters,

51
00:04:26,630 --> 00:04:29,600
these are all the buildings
handled by our firm.

52
00:04:29,600 --> 00:04:31,740
I see.

53
00:04:33,980 --> 00:04:35,980
- You design hot springs as well?
- Yeah.

54
00:04:35,980 --> 00:04:38,000
It's an open air bath.

55
00:04:43,130 --> 00:04:45,340
What a cute store.

56
00:04:48,700 --> 00:04:50,550
Thanks.

57
00:04:50,550 --> 00:04:52,800
I designed that one myself.

58
00:04:52,800 --> 00:04:54,770
What?

59
00:04:54,770 --> 00:04:56,970
Mao's an officially licensed architect.

60
00:04:56,970 --> 00:04:58,940
He passed the exam on his first try.

61
00:04:58,940 --> 00:05:00,800
Really?

62
00:05:00,800 --> 00:05:02,680
That's amazing.

63
00:05:02,680 --> 00:05:05,780
I studied hard.

64
00:05:07,200 --> 00:05:10,660
We passed these buildings on our way here.
Did you notice?

65
00:05:10,660 --> 00:05:12,200
What?

66
00:05:17,320 --> 00:05:20,000
The shortcut doesn't save much time,

67
00:05:20,000 --> 00:05:22,790
but it's a nicer view.

68
00:05:23,600 --> 00:05:25,270
I see.

69
00:05:27,750 --> 00:05:31,990
<i>What do you think of the night we shared?</i>

70
00:05:31,990 --> 00:05:35,050
<i>Why won't you ask me anything?</i>

71
00:05:37,000 --> 00:05:40,230
<i>I certainly can't ask these questions now.</i>

72
00:05:44,040 --> 00:05:45,770
What's up?

73
00:05:48,100 --> 00:05:50,510
Sorry, it's nothing.

74
00:05:50,510 --> 00:05:52,110
If you insist.

75
00:05:53,380 --> 00:05:58,070
By the way, this is the building
we're handling right now.

76
00:06:11,810 --> 00:06:13,990
Oh.
[Memo]

77
00:06:15,110 --> 00:06:18,090
I write there when I can't find a notepad.

78
00:06:19,240 --> 00:06:21,270
You must be glad it didn't fade away.

79
00:06:21,270 --> 00:06:22,780
Yeah.

80
00:06:26,640 --> 00:06:29,610
I wonder if Monou is Mao's type.

81
00:06:29,610 --> 00:06:30,770
Huh?

82
00:06:30,770 --> 00:06:33,070
I mean, he's being extra kind to her.

83
00:06:35,400 --> 00:06:38,420
You know that's just who Mao is.

84
00:06:40,440 --> 00:06:42,920
Is that really all there is to it?

85
00:06:44,610 --> 00:06:49,990
Tsukidome. Thank you,
but I'll learn the rest on my own.

86
00:06:51,720 --> 00:06:53,220
Just call me Mao.

87
00:06:53,220 --> 00:06:55,610
No formalities needed.

88
00:06:55,610 --> 00:06:58,680
You're the same age as Erika, right?

89
00:06:58,680 --> 00:07:01,490
That means I'm several years your junior.

90
00:07:01,490 --> 00:07:03,710
Several? How old are you?

91
00:07:03,710 --> 00:07:05,610
I'm 26 years old.

92
00:07:07,250 --> 00:07:09,740
Six years my junior?

93
00:07:16,170 --> 00:07:17,930
Hello?

94
00:07:18,960 --> 00:07:20,470
What?

95
00:07:20,470 --> 00:07:22,190
You found Sui?

96
00:07:22,190 --> 00:07:23,350
Yes!

97
00:07:23,350 --> 00:07:25,560
Awesome.

98
00:07:26,700 --> 00:07:28,680
Where is she?

99
00:07:32,460 --> 00:07:34,420
Congrats on your first day!

100
00:07:34,420 --> 00:07:36,620
Cheers!

101
00:07:39,580 --> 00:07:41,400
That hits the spot.

102
00:07:42,680 --> 00:07:44,760
So, how was it?

103
00:07:44,760 --> 00:07:48,370
Everyone was so kind. I felt right at home.

104
00:07:50,800 --> 00:07:51,840
Say...

105
00:07:51,840 --> 00:07:53,380
Yeah?

106
00:07:55,620 --> 00:07:56,860
No, never mind.

107
00:07:56,860 --> 00:07:59,790
Now I'm extra curious.

108
00:08:02,490 --> 00:08:04,520
Well...

109
00:08:06,320 --> 00:08:10,320
I thought I'd try to become
a licensed interior designer.

110
00:08:10,320 --> 00:08:13,120
Great idea! You've got the eye for it,

111
00:08:13,120 --> 00:08:16,520
so I always thought you should go for it.

112
00:08:16,520 --> 00:08:18,990
This is all thanks to your introduction.

113
00:08:18,990 --> 00:08:21,530
I really can't thank you enough.

114
00:08:21,530 --> 00:08:23,910
It's my pleasure to help.

115
00:08:24,680 --> 00:08:27,260
Mao's grown up, hasn't he?

116
00:08:28,420 --> 00:08:30,380
Huh? You don't remember him?

117
00:08:30,380 --> 00:08:32,570
You two met, long ago.

118
00:08:32,570 --> 00:08:34,620
- We did?
- Yeah.

119
00:08:34,620 --> 00:08:37,430
Back when he was in elementary school.

120
00:08:37,430 --> 00:08:40,600
Yeah, but I'm not sure.

121
00:08:40,600 --> 00:08:44,340
Maybe I'm not confident enough...

122
00:08:45,020 --> 00:08:47,870
Hello there.

123
00:08:50,720 --> 00:08:53,470
The kid who would always hid behind you?

124
00:08:53,470 --> 00:08:58,030
Yeah. He used to be such a downer.

125
00:09:00,850 --> 00:09:02,600
What about now?

126
00:09:03,670 --> 00:09:05,740
What's he like now?

127
00:09:08,800 --> 00:09:12,140
No, it's not like that.

128
00:09:12,140 --> 00:09:13,730
Really now.

129
00:09:13,730 --> 00:09:16,100
I'm telling you, it's not.

130
00:09:16,100 --> 00:09:17,830
I haven't said anything yet.

131
00:09:17,830 --> 00:09:21,040
Erika.

132
00:09:21,040 --> 00:09:23,560
Stop that.

133
00:09:23,560 --> 00:09:25,310
Jeez...

134
00:09:25,310 --> 00:09:27,420
I'm pulling your leg.

135
00:09:27,420 --> 00:09:29,860
Let's see...

136
00:09:29,860 --> 00:09:31,580
Now, he's a dude obsessed

137
00:09:31,580 --> 00:09:35,540
with helping people in need.

138
00:09:36,860 --> 00:09:38,860
I see.

139
00:09:40,790 --> 00:09:42,350
That reminds me.

140
00:09:43,820 --> 00:09:47,590
I got these from my relatives.
Take them with you.

141
00:09:47,590 --> 00:09:48,910
Hup.

142
00:09:48,910 --> 00:09:52,180
Never skimp on veggies,
even if you're living solo.

143
00:09:54,790 --> 00:09:56,590
This is a lot.

144
00:10:05,810 --> 00:10:07,460
I'll carry those.

145
00:10:07,460 --> 00:10:09,440
Thank you.

146
00:10:10,480 --> 00:10:14,670
I'm sorry for causing you so much trouble.

147
00:10:14,670 --> 00:10:17,120
I'm just carrying your vegetables.

148
00:10:17,120 --> 00:10:19,990
That's not the only "trouble"
I was referring to...

149
00:10:33,040 --> 00:10:34,940
- Here.
- Thank you.

150
00:10:36,890 --> 00:10:39,020
Good night.

151
00:10:39,020 --> 00:10:42,030
Thanks again. Good night.

152
00:10:47,940 --> 00:10:50,270
<i>Your door is now unlocked.</i>

153
00:10:52,520 --> 00:10:56,480
Maybe he is just nice.

154
00:10:59,200 --> 00:11:01,440
<i>Your door is now unlocked.</i>

155
00:11:08,300 --> 00:11:11,060
[Idea Construction Office]

156
00:11:11,060 --> 00:11:12,200
Sui.

157
00:11:12,200 --> 00:11:13,430
Long time no see.

158
00:11:13,430 --> 00:11:14,990
Why are you here?

159
00:11:14,990 --> 00:11:16,700
I missed you.

160
00:11:16,700 --> 00:11:18,250
What?

161
00:11:21,820 --> 00:11:23,140
You okay?

162
00:11:23,140 --> 00:11:24,640
Yeah.

163
00:11:26,790 --> 00:11:29,800
Don't be such a stranger.

164
00:11:29,800 --> 00:11:32,690
- We were engaged!
- And we have work to do.

165
00:11:32,690 --> 00:11:34,420
"We"?

166
00:11:37,610 --> 00:11:41,590
Himukai, you'll be late if you don't hurry.

167
00:11:52,130 --> 00:11:54,540
Fine. I'll leave for the day.

168
00:11:54,540 --> 00:11:57,940
Let's chat again some other time.

169
00:11:57,940 --> 00:11:59,540
See you!

170
00:12:07,390 --> 00:12:11,580
Thank you.

171
00:12:14,280 --> 00:12:16,970
Arguing with the boyfriend first thing?

172
00:12:16,970 --> 00:12:18,970
Not appropriate, Matsubara.

173
00:12:18,970 --> 00:12:20,470
Right, sorry.

174
00:12:20,470 --> 00:12:24,150
Popular girls sure have it rough.

175
00:12:39,100 --> 00:12:41,260
We've drafted designs
for the Kawasaki branch,

176
00:12:41,260 --> 00:12:44,720
so could you choose flooring
and tables for the place?

177
00:12:44,720 --> 00:12:47,290
I have a meeting now,

178
00:12:47,290 --> 00:12:48,850
but I'll check in with you tomorrow.

179
00:12:48,850 --> 00:12:52,700
- I'm excited to work with you.
- Likewise.

180
00:13:01,220 --> 00:13:04,560
Did you need something else?

181
00:13:06,540 --> 00:13:09,720
You seemed to be in a pinch this morning.

182
00:13:09,720 --> 00:13:12,120
Was everything all right?

183
00:13:12,120 --> 00:13:15,610
Yes. I'm sorry to worry you, Mizuno.

184
00:13:15,610 --> 00:13:16,760
Don't be.

185
00:13:16,760 --> 00:13:20,640
I've dealt with a stalker before,

186
00:13:20,640 --> 00:13:23,790
so I want to make sure you're careful.

187
00:13:23,790 --> 00:13:27,640
I don't think he's necessarily a stalker,

188
00:13:27,640 --> 00:13:29,660
but I appreciate warning.

189
00:13:29,660 --> 00:13:31,520
Mizuno, ready to head out?

190
00:13:31,520 --> 00:13:33,880
Yup. Then I'll leave the rest to you.

191
00:13:33,880 --> 00:13:35,470
Sure.

192
00:13:36,760 --> 00:13:38,290
Ready?

193
00:13:52,150 --> 00:13:54,740
That's a new bracelet, isn't it?

194
00:13:54,740 --> 00:13:56,100
Oh, this?

195
00:13:59,080 --> 00:14:02,420
Was it a present from your girlfriend?

196
00:14:02,420 --> 00:14:05,070
If only.

197
00:14:05,070 --> 00:14:07,770
What? But...

198
00:14:17,140 --> 00:14:19,900
We've already been apart for two years now.

199
00:14:21,650 --> 00:14:24,940
I'm gonna grab a drink. Want something?

200
00:14:24,940 --> 00:14:26,940
I'm fine, thank you.

201
00:14:26,940 --> 00:14:28,940
All right. I'll be right back.

202
00:14:32,600 --> 00:14:34,740
A one-night stand?

203
00:14:43,960 --> 00:14:46,600
[Family History]

204
00:14:50,770 --> 00:14:54,790
This herbal tea is great
for alleviating stress, and insomnia.

205
00:14:54,790 --> 00:14:56,700
Give it a try.

206
00:14:56,700 --> 00:14:59,440
Thank you, Takizawa.

207
00:15:09,250 --> 00:15:14,570
I'm worried about you, Himukai.

208
00:15:16,020 --> 00:15:19,260
Sorry. I just can't forget about Sui.

209
00:15:20,140 --> 00:15:22,870
I know I'm the one who dumped her,

210
00:15:23,540 --> 00:15:27,150
but did she really have to act so cold?

211
00:15:27,150 --> 00:15:29,160
She's so cruel!

212
00:15:33,100 --> 00:15:36,440
Don't worry, Himukai.

213
00:15:36,440 --> 00:15:39,320
I have a brilliant idea, just for you.

214
00:15:41,950 --> 00:15:43,740
A brilliant idea?

215
00:15:45,020 --> 00:15:48,810
I also love Sui.

216
00:15:48,810 --> 00:15:52,910
And I want things to work out for you two.

217
00:15:52,910 --> 00:15:55,580
Always have.

218
00:15:57,020 --> 00:15:58,690
Really?

219
00:16:00,940 --> 00:16:03,210
Want to hear my brilliant scheme?

220
00:16:03,210 --> 00:16:09,650
It'll bring you two back together again.

221
00:16:11,720 --> 00:16:15,030
A scheme, to bring us back together?

222
00:16:18,060 --> 00:16:21,110
[Monou]
[Ioka]

223
00:16:28,670 --> 00:16:32,560
I can't believe I used to live here.

224
00:16:36,110 --> 00:16:37,980
Cute, right?

225
00:16:37,980 --> 00:16:39,830
I gave them a quick rinse.

226
00:16:39,830 --> 00:16:42,050
A rinse? Why?

227
00:16:42,770 --> 00:16:47,880
You're so clueless about pregnancy.

228
00:16:47,880 --> 00:16:51,470
Even if they're new,
baby clothes need to be rinsed

229
00:16:51,470 --> 00:16:54,030
so the fabric doesn't irritate their skin.

230
00:16:55,700 --> 00:16:59,130
Make sure you're taking notes for yourself.

231
00:17:01,820 --> 00:17:03,730
I'll make us some tea.

232
00:17:03,730 --> 00:17:05,410
- How does black tea sound?
- Great, thanks.

233
00:17:06,290 --> 00:17:10,420
Just make sure it's the decaffeinated stuff.

234
00:17:12,550 --> 00:17:15,520
You're so conscious of your baby.

235
00:17:15,520 --> 00:17:17,530
Of course. They're my child.

236
00:17:17,530 --> 00:17:20,430
You'll get it when your time comes, too.

237
00:17:20,430 --> 00:17:21,600
Think so?

238
00:17:21,600 --> 00:17:23,870
Yeah, you will.

239
00:17:24,920 --> 00:17:28,650
Are you not interested in having kids?

240
00:17:29,260 --> 00:17:31,020
That's not exactly it.

241
00:17:31,020 --> 00:17:35,050
Then you're better off knowing these things.

242
00:17:35,820 --> 00:17:39,110
How about we study up on pregnancy together?

243
00:17:45,910 --> 00:17:47,370
Sui.

244
00:17:48,310 --> 00:17:52,210
Are you thinking about your future?

245
00:17:52,210 --> 00:17:53,610
Huh?

246
00:17:55,840 --> 00:17:59,750
I'm really happy with my life right now.

247
00:18:00,390 --> 00:18:04,280
That's why I want you to become happy, too.

248
00:18:04,280 --> 00:18:07,710
I know you sacrificed a lot for me,

249
00:18:07,710 --> 00:18:10,710
and you always put yourself second.

250
00:18:10,710 --> 00:18:12,360
Rin...

251
00:18:14,850 --> 00:18:17,240
Sui, be honest, am I the reason why

252
00:18:17,240 --> 00:18:19,450
you broke off the engagement?

253
00:18:19,450 --> 00:18:21,300
What are you talking about?

254
00:18:21,300 --> 00:18:23,240
You know that's not true.

255
00:18:23,240 --> 00:18:25,150
But...

256
00:18:28,620 --> 00:18:32,750
Okay. Then you really are
thinking about your future?

257
00:18:32,750 --> 00:18:36,500
You haven't given up
on your own happiness, right?

258
00:18:40,830 --> 00:18:45,340
Of course not.
I changed jobs for that very reason.

259
00:18:52,280 --> 00:18:56,210
Sui, I'm always here for you, okay?

260
00:18:57,000 --> 00:19:01,860
Promise me you'll take your marriage
and future kids seriously.

261
00:19:11,380 --> 00:19:15,330
<i>Let's make sure our kids
become best friends, okay?</i>

262
00:19:15,330 --> 00:19:19,940
<i>They're practically saying
you've failed as a woman.</i>

263
00:19:19,940 --> 00:19:23,580
<i>I mean, infertile? After seven years together?</i>

264
00:19:23,580 --> 00:19:26,500
<i>You ought to be more wary. You're a woman.</i>

265
00:19:42,630 --> 00:19:45,160
Himukai?

266
00:19:45,160 --> 00:19:47,380
Why are you...

267
00:19:47,380 --> 00:19:50,740
I'm sorry about the other day.
I wasn't in my right mind.

268
00:19:55,790 --> 00:19:58,840
But I want you to listen to me.

269
00:19:58,840 --> 00:20:02,130
I can't give up on you, Sui.

270
00:20:03,440 --> 00:20:06,920
N-Not here.

271
00:20:25,170 --> 00:20:27,470
<i>Your door is now unlocked.</i>

272
00:20:30,320 --> 00:20:32,770
Thanks for having me.

273
00:20:43,570 --> 00:20:46,290
I'll convince my parents.

274
00:20:46,290 --> 00:20:48,930
I don't need any kids.

275
00:20:48,930 --> 00:20:51,210
Sui, you're the one who's important to me.

276
00:20:51,210 --> 00:20:52,920
You get that, right?

277
00:20:55,860 --> 00:20:57,650
Sui, I love you.

278
00:20:57,650 --> 00:20:59,110
Hey!

279
00:20:59,110 --> 00:21:00,880
What's wrong?

280
00:21:02,220 --> 00:21:03,970
We broke up.

281
00:21:03,970 --> 00:21:05,540
We broke up?

282
00:21:05,540 --> 00:21:07,740
But I still love you.

283
00:21:07,740 --> 00:21:11,350
You haven't been able to
forget me either, right?

284
00:21:15,230 --> 00:21:16,810
So, why...

285
00:21:16,810 --> 00:21:20,310
Why did you have to be infertile?

286
00:21:22,680 --> 00:21:25,430
You messed everything up.

287
00:21:26,810 --> 00:21:29,000
Are you saying this is my fault?

288
00:21:29,000 --> 00:21:31,500
But if marriage isn't on the table,

289
00:21:31,500 --> 00:21:34,530
I don't have to give up on you.

290
00:21:34,530 --> 00:21:38,590
- What?
- I said the marriage was off, sure.

291
00:21:38,590 --> 00:21:39,950
But I never said we'd break up.

292
00:21:39,950 --> 00:21:42,800
You want to stay with me too, don't you?

293
00:21:45,840 --> 00:21:48,360
Even if I marry another woman,

294
00:21:48,360 --> 00:21:52,040
I can continue seeing you.

295
00:21:53,130 --> 00:21:54,170
You're not making any sense.

296
00:21:54,170 --> 00:21:57,900
Don't you get it? You dummy.

297
00:21:57,900 --> 00:22:02,330
I just can't have kids with you.

298
00:22:02,330 --> 00:22:05,390
Since you're infertile,
it'll work out perfectly.

299
00:22:31,740 --> 00:22:34,360
Come back to me, Sui.

300
00:22:35,610 --> 00:22:38,560
I'll process your company paperwork.

301
00:22:39,250 --> 00:22:40,980
Let's give this another shot.

302
00:22:43,110 --> 00:22:44,990
No.

303
00:22:49,450 --> 00:22:52,900
Right, you're mad at me.

304
00:22:55,140 --> 00:22:58,540
I'm sorry I forced you to quit.

305
00:22:58,540 --> 00:23:00,740
But that was Mom and Dad's decision.

306
00:23:00,740 --> 00:23:03,680
So, forgive me, yeah?

307
00:23:08,180 --> 00:23:10,430
Don't worry.

308
00:23:10,430 --> 00:23:12,750
Making up is the easiest part.

309
00:23:12,750 --> 00:23:14,690
Get off.

310
00:23:14,690 --> 00:23:17,310
Don't touch me!

311
00:23:19,690 --> 00:23:23,790
You're the one who let me into your room.

312
00:23:23,790 --> 00:23:26,640
- Stop!
- Quit resisting already.

313
00:23:27,280 --> 00:23:29,380
Stop, please!

314
00:23:29,380 --> 00:23:31,720
- Sui.
- Get off of her.

315
00:23:47,030 --> 00:23:49,150
Let's get married.

316
00:23:49,150 --> 00:23:52,570
I promise to bear a healthy heir for you.

317
00:23:52,570 --> 00:23:55,640
If you're anxious, I can stay here with you.

318
00:23:55,640 --> 00:23:56,640
I'll be fine.

319
00:23:56,640 --> 00:23:58,370
Why?

320
00:23:58,370 --> 00:24:00,680
You don't have to ignore your resentment.
